# ========================================================================
# ‚úÖ SAFE TO COMMIT (Examples for reference)
# ========================================================================

# These files SHOULD be committed:
# README.md
# SETUP_GUIDE.md
# .env.example
# docker-compose-coolify.yml
# docker-compose.yml
# mail-template/*.html (template files without real data)
# .gitignore (this file)

# ========================================================================
# üìã IMPORTANT NOTES
# ========================================================================

# 1. Always review files before committing
# 2. Use 'git status' to check what's being tracked
# 3. Use 'git add .' carefully - prefer explicit file names
# 4. If you accidentally commit secrets:
#    - Change all passwords/keys immediately
#    - Use git-filter-branch or BFG to clean history
#    - Force push to update remote repository
#
# 5. For team collaboration:
#    - Share .env.example instead of .env
#    - Document any additional files that need local configuration
#    - Use secure channels for sharing actual credentials
#
# ========================================================================